main event: Two objects connected, side by side, were observed in the sky over Tillamook, Oregon, in June 1960.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 6-10 seconds., The objects appeared rectangular and emitted bright lights., Witnesses speculated that the objects could have been balloons or a meteor., The sighting was reported from a control tower at Portland International Airport., The conditions were calm and clear at the time of the observation.
sighted object: two bright lights connected side by side
witness description: Control tower operator, qualified and experienced.
